In a press gaggle, Press Secretary Jay Carney announces that Taiwan has been designated as the newest member of the Visa Waiver Program, allowing secure and expedited travel for eligible Taiwan passport holders to the United States. Carney also addresses questions about Mitt Romney's offshore holdings and tax havens, the security situation in Benghazi, immigration reform, sequestration, and the President's debate preparation. The press secretary also comments on the impact of sanctions on the Iranian economy and the instability in Iraq. The press gaggle ends with questions about the Pennsylvania voter ID law and the President's debate preparation with Senator John Kerry.